reference.title: AArch64 registers by functional group
reference.shortdesc: This section identifies the AArch64 registers by their functional groups and applies to the registers in the core that are implementation defined or have micro-architectural bit fields. Reset values are provided for these registers.

p.xref: AIDR_EL1, Auxiliary ID Register, EL1AIDR_EL1 provides IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED identification information. This register is not used in the Cortexâ€‘A76 core.
CCSIDR_EL1, Cache Size ID Register, EL1The CCSIDR_EL1 provides information about the architecture of the currently selected cache.
CLIDR_EL1, Cache Level ID Register, EL1The CLIDR_EL1 identifies the type of cache, or caches, implemented at each level, up to a maximum of seven levels.
CSSELR_EL1, Cache Size Selection Register, EL1CSSELR_EL1 selects the current Cache Size ID Register (CCSIDR_EL1), by specifying:
CTR_EL0, Cache Type Register, EL0The CTR_EL0 provides information about the architecture of the caches.

entry.xref: DCZID_EL0, Data Cache Zero ID Register, EL0The DCZID_EL0 indicates the block size written with byte values of zero by the DC ZVA (Data Cache Zero by Address) system instruction.
ERRIDR_EL1, Error ID Register, EL1The ERRIDR_EL1 defines the number of error record registers.
ID_AA64AFR0_EL1, AArch64 Auxiliary Feature Register 0The does not use this register, ID_AA64AFR0_EL1 is RES0.
ID_AA64AFR1_EL1, Auxiliary Feature Register 1The does not use this register, ID_AA64AFR0_EL1 is RES0.

p.xref: ID_AA64DFR0_EL1, Debug Feature Register 0, EL1Provides top-level information about the debug system in .

entry.xref: ID_AA64DFR1_EL1, Debug Feature Register 1, EL1This register is reserved for future expansion of top level information about the debug system in state.

ul.li: 0000100010211120 if the Cryptographic Extension is implemented.
0000100010210000 if the Cryptographic Extension is not implemented.

p.xref: ID_AA64ISAR0_EL1, Instruction Set Attribute Register 0, EL1The ID_AA64ISAR0_EL1 provides information about the instructions implemented in state, including the instructions that are provided by the Cryptographic Extension.
ID_AA64ISAR1_EL1, Instruction Set Attribute Register 1, EL1The ID_AA64ISAR1_EL1 provides information about the instructions implemented in state.
ID_AA64MMFR0_EL1, Memory Model Feature Register 0, EL1The ID_AA64MMFR0_EL1 provides information about the implemented memory model and memory management support in the Execution state.
ID_AA64MMFR1_EL1, Memory Model Feature Register 1, EL1The ID_AA64MMFR1_EL1 provides information about the implemented memory model and memory management support in the Execution state.
ID_AA64MMFR2_EL1, Memory Model Feature Register 2, EL1The ID_AA64MMFR2_EL1 provides information about the implemented memory model and memory management support in the Execution state.

ul.li: 1100000010111112 if the GICv4 interface is disabled.
1100000011111112 if the v4 interface is enabled.

p.xref: ID_AA64PFR0_EL1, Processor Feature Register 0, EL1The ID_AA64PFR0_EL1 provides additional information about implemented features in .

entry.xref: ID_AA64PFR1_EL1, Processor Feature Register 1, EL1The ID_AA64PFR1_EL1 provides additional information about implemented features in .

p.xref: ID_AFR0_EL1, AArch32 Auxiliary Feature Register 0, EL1The ID_AFR0_EL1 provides information about the IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED features of the PE in . This register is not used in the Cortexâ€‘A76 .
ID_DFR0_EL1, Debug Feature Register 0, EL1The ID_DFR0_EL1 provides top-level information about the debug system in .
ID_ISAR0_EL1, Instruction Set Attribute Register 0, EL1The ID_ISAR0_EL1 provides information about the instruction sets implemented by the in .
ID_ISAR1_EL1, Instruction Set Attribute Register 1, EL1The ID_ISAR1_EL1 provides information about the instruction sets implemented by the in .
ID_ISAR2_EL1, Instruction Set Attribute Register 2, EL1The ID_ISAR2_EL1 provides information about the instruction sets implemented by the in .
ID_ISAR3_EL1, Instruction Set Attribute Register 3, EL1The ID_ISAR3_EL1 provides information about the instruction sets implemented by the in .
ID_ISAR4_EL1, Instruction Set Attribute Register 4, EL1The ID_ISAR4_EL1 provides information about the instruction sets implemented by the in .

entry.p: ID_ISAR5 has the value 01010001 if the Cryptographic Extension is not implemented and enabled.

p.xref: ID_ISAR5_EL1, Instruction Set Attribute Register 5, EL1The ID_ISAR5_EL1 provides information about the instruction sets that the implements.
ID_ISAR6_EL1, Instruction Set Attribute Register 6, EL1The ID_ISAR6_EL1 provides information about the instruction sets that the implements.
ID_MMFR0_EL1, Memory Model Feature Register 0, EL1The ID_MMFR0_EL1 provides information about the memory model and memory management support in .
ID_MMFR1_EL1, Memory Model Feature Register 1, EL1The ID_MMFR1_EL1 provides information about the memory model and memory management support in .
ID_MMFR2_EL1, Memory Model Feature Register 2, EL1The ID_MMFR2_EL1 provides information about the implemented memory model and memory management support in .
ID_MMFR3_EL1, Memory Model Feature Register 3, EL1The ID_MMFR3_EL1 provides information about the memory model and memory management support in .
ID_MMFR4_EL1, Memory Model Feature Register 4, EL1The ID_MMFR4_EL1 provides information about the memory model and memory management support in .
ID_PFR0_EL1, Processor Feature Register 0, EL1The ID_PFR0_EL1 provides top-level information about the instruction sets supported by the in .

entry.p: Bits [31:28] are 1 if the CPU interface is implemented and enabled, and 0 otherwise.

p.xref: ID_PFR1_EL1, Processor Feature Register 1, EL1The ID_PFR1_EL1 provides information about the programmers model and architecture extensions supported by the .
ID_PFR2_EL1, Processor Feature Register 2, EL1The ID_PFR2_EL1 provides information about the programmers model and architecture extensions supported by the .
LORID_EL1, LORegion ID Register, EL1The LORID_EL1 ID register indicates the supported number of LORegions and LORegion descriptors.
MIDR_EL1, Main ID Register, EL1The MIDR_EL1 provides identification information for the , including an implementer code for the device and a ID number.

entry.p: The reset value depends on CLUSTERIDAFF2[7:0] and CLUSTERIDAFF3[7:0]. See register description for details.

p.xref: MPIDR_EL1, Multiprocessor Affinity Register, EL1The MPIDR_EL1 provides an additional identification mechanism for scheduling purposes in a cluster.

REVIDR_EL1, Revision ID Register, EL1The REVIDR_EL1 provides revision information, additional to MIDR_EL1, that identifies minor fixes (errata) which might be present in a specific implementation of the Cortexâ€‘A76 .

entry.p: The reset value is the value of MPIDR_EL1.
The reset value is the value of MIDR_EL1.

p.xref: ACTLR_EL1, Auxiliary Control Register, EL1ACTLR_EL1 provides IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED configuration and control options for execution at EL1 and EL0.
ACTLR_EL2, Auxiliary Control Register, EL2The ACTLR_EL2 provides IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED configuration and control options for EL2.
ACTLR_EL3, Auxiliary Control Register, EL3The ACTLR_EL3 provides IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED configuration and control options for EL3.
CCR_EL1, Architectural Feature Access Control Register, EL1The CCR_EL1 controls access to trace functionality and access to registers associated with Advanced SIMD and floating-point execution.
SCTLR_EL1, System Control Register, EL1The SCTLR_EL1 provides top-level control of the system, including its memory system, at EL1 and EL0.
SCTLR_EL2, System Control Register, EL2The SCTLR_EL2 provides top-level control of the system, including its memory system at EL2.
SCTLR_EL3, System Control Register, EL3The SCTLR_EL3 provides top-level control of the system, including its memory system at EL3.
SCTLR_EL1, System Control Register, EL1The SCTLR_EL1 provides top-level control of the system, including its memory system, at EL1 and EL0.
DISR_EL1, Deferred Interrupt Status Register, EL1The DISR_EL1 records the SError interrupts consumed by an ESB instruction.
ERRIDR_EL1, Error ID Register, EL1The ERRIDR_EL1 defines the number of error record registers.
ERRSELR_EL1, Error Record Select Register, EL1The ERRSELR_EL1 selects which error record should be accessed through the Error Record system registers. This register is not reset on a warm reset.
ERXADDR_EL1, Selected Error Record Address Register, EL1Register ERXADDR_EL1 accesses the ERR<n>ADDR address register for the error record selected by ERRSELR_EL1.SEL.
ERXCTLR_EL1, Selected Error Record Control Register, EL1Register ERXCTLR_EL1 accesses the ERR<n>CTLR control register for the error record selected by ERRSELR_EL1.SEL.
ERXFR_EL1, Selected Error Record Feature Register, EL1Register ERXFR_EL1 accesses the ERR<n>FR feature register for the error record selected by ERRSELR_EL1.SEL.
ERXMISC0_EL1, Selected Error Record Miscellaneous Register 0, EL1Register ERXMISC0_EL1 accesses the ERR<n>MISC0 register for the error record selected by ERRSELR_EL1.SEL.
ERXMISC1_EL1, Selected Error Record Miscellaneous Register 1, EL1Register ERXMISC1_EL1 accesses the ERR<n>MISC1 miscellaneous register 1 for the error record selected by ERRSELR_EL1.SEL.
ERXSTATUS_EL1, Selected Error Record Primary Status Register, EL1Register ERXSTATUS_EL1 accesses the ERR<n>STATUS primary status register for the error record selected by ERRSELR_EL1.SEL.
ERXPFGCDN_EL1, Selected Error Pseudo Fault Generation Count Down Register, EL1Register ERXPFGCDN_EL1 accesses the ERR<n>PFGCND register for the error record selected by ERRSELR_EL1.SEL.
ERXPFGCTL_EL1, Selected Error Pseudo Fault Generation Control Register, EL1Register ERXPFGCTL_EL1 accesses the ERR<n>PFGCTL register for the error record selected by ERRSELR_EL1.SEL.
ERXPFGF_EL1, Selected Pseudo Fault Generation Feature Register, EL1Register ERXPFGF_EL1 accesses the ERR<n>PFGF register for the error record selected by ERRSELR_EL1.SEL.
HCR_EL2, Hypervisor Configuration Register, EL2The HCR_EL2 provides configuration control for virtualization, including whether various Non-secure operations are trapped to EL2.
VDISR_EL2, Virtual Deferred Interrupt Status Register, EL2The VDISR_EL2 records that a virtual SError interrupt has been consumed by an ESB instruction executed at Non-secure EL1.
VSESR_EL2, Virtual SError Exception Syndrome Register (Ares Specific)The VSESR_EL2 provides the syndrome value reported to software on taking a virtual SError interrupt exception.

AMAIR_EL1, Auxiliary Memory Attribute Indirection Register, EL1AMAIR_EL1 provides IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED memory attributes for the memory regions specified by MAIR_EL1. This register is not used in the Cortexâ€‘A76 .

AMAIR_EL2, Auxiliary Memory Attribute Indirection Register, EL2AMAIR_EL2 provides IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED memory attributes for the memory s specified by MAIR_EL2. This register is not used in the Cortexâ€‘A76 .

AMAIR_EL3, Auxiliary Memory Attribute Indirection Register, EL3AMAIR_EL3 provides IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED memory attributes for the memory s specified by MAIR_EL3. This register is not used in the Cortexâ€‘A76 .
LORC_EL1, LORegion Control Register, EL1The LORC_EL1 register enables and disables LORegions, and selects the current LORegion descriptor.
LORID_EL1, LORegion ID Register, EL1The LORID_EL1 ID register indicates the supported number of LORegions and LORegion descriptors.
LORN_EL1, LORegion Number Register, EL1The LORN_EL1 register holds the number of the LORegion described in the current LORegion descriptor selected by LORC_EL1.DS.

TCR_EL1, Translation Control Register, EL1The TCR_EL1 determines which Translation Base registers define the base address register for a translation table walk required for stage 1 translation of a memory access from EL0 or EL1 and holds cacheability and shareability information.
TCR_EL2, Translation Control Register, EL2The TCR_EL2 controls walks required for stage 1 translation of a memory access from EL2 and holds cacheability and shareability information.
TCR_EL3, Translation Control Register, EL3The TCR_EL3 controls walks required for stage 1 translation of memory accesses from EL3 and holds cacheability and shareability information for the accesses.

TTBR0_EL1, Translation Table Base Register 0, EL1The TTBR0_EL1 holds the base address of 0, and information about the memory it occupies. This is one of the s for the stage 1 translation of memory accesses from modes other than Hyp mode.
TTBR0_EL2, Translation Table Base Register 0, EL2The TTBR0_EL2 holds the base address of the for the stage 1 translation of memory accesses from EL2.
TTBR0_EL3, Translation Table Base Register 0, EL3The TTBR0_EL3 holds the base address of the for the stage 1 translation of memory accesses from EL3.

TTBR1_EL1, Translation Table Base Register 1, EL1The TTBR1_EL1 holds the base address of 1, and information about the memory it occupies. This is one of the s for the stage 1 translation of memory accesses at EL0 and EL1.
TTBR1_EL2, Translation Table Base Register 1, EL2TTBR1_EL2 has the same format and contents as TTBR1_EL1.
VTTBR_EL2, Virtualization Translation Table Base Register, EL2VTTBR_EL2 holds the base address of the for the stage 2 translation of memory accesses from Non-secure EL0 and EL1.
ACTLR_EL2, Auxiliary Control Register, EL2The ACTLR_EL2 provides IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED configuration and control options for EL2.
AFSR0_EL2, Auxiliary Fault Status Register 0, EL2AFSR0_EL2 provides additional IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED fault status information for s that are taken to EL2.
AFSR1_EL2, Auxiliary Fault Status Register 1, EL2AFSR1_EL2 provides additional IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED status information for s that are taken to EL2. This register is not used in the Cortexâ€‘A76 .

AMAIR_EL2, Auxiliary Memory Attribute Indirection Register, EL2AMAIR_EL2 provides IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED memory attributes for the memory s specified by MAIR_EL2. This register is not used in the Cortexâ€‘A76 .

CPTR_EL2, Architectural Feature Trap Register, EL2The CPTR_EL2 controls trapping to EL2 for accesses to CCR, trace functionality and registers associated with and execution. It also controls EL2 access to this functionality.
ESR_EL2, Exception Syndrome Register, EL2The ESR_EL2 holds syndrome information for an taken to EL2.

HACR_EL2, Hyp Auxiliary Configuration Register, EL2HACR_EL2 controls trapping to EL2 of IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED aspects of Non-secure EL1 or EL0 operation. This register is not used in the Cortexâ€‘A76 .
HCR_EL2, Hypervisor Configuration Register, EL2The HCR_EL2 provides configuration control for virtualization, including whether various Non-secure operations are trapped to EL2.

VTCR_EL2, Virtualization Translation Control Register, EL2The VTCR_EL2 controls the walks required for the stage 2 translation of memory accesses from Non-secure EL0 and EL1.

p.xref: VTTBR_EL2, Virtualization Translation Table Base Register, EL2VTTBR_EL2 holds the base address of the for the stage 2 translation of memory accesses from Non-secure EL0 and EL1.

AFSR1_EL3, Auxiliary Fault Status Register 1, EL3AFSR1_EL3 provides additional IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED status information for s that are taken to EL3. This register is not used in the Cortexâ€‘A76 .
DISR_EL1, Deferred Interrupt Status Register, EL1The DISR_EL1 records the SError interrupts consumed by an ESB instruction.

ESR_EL2, Exception Syndrome Register, EL2The ESR_EL2 holds syndrome information for an taken to EL2.
ESR_EL3, Exception Syndrome Register, EL3The ESR_EL3 holds syndrome information for an taken to EL3.
VDISR_EL2, Virtual Deferred Interrupt Status Register, EL2The VDISR_EL2 records that a virtual SError interrupt has been consumed by an ESB instruction executed at Non-secure EL1.
VSESR_EL2, Virtual SError Exception Syndrome Register (Ares Specific)The VSESR_EL2 provides the syndrome value reported to software on taking a virtual SError interrupt .
CPUACTLR_EL1, CPU Auxiliary Control Register, EL1The CPUACTLR_EL1 provides IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED configuration and control options for the .
CPUACTLR2_EL1, CPU Auxiliary Control Register 2, EL1The CPUACTLR2_EL1 provides IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED configuration and control options for the .
CPUCFR_EL1, CPU Configuration Register, EL1The CPUCFR_EL1 provides configuration information for the .
CPUECTLR_EL1, CPU Extended Control Register, EL1The CPUECTLR_EL1 provides additional IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED configuration and control options for the .
CPUPWRCTLR_EL1, Power Control Register, EL1The CPUPWRCTLR_EL1 provides information about power control support for the .
ERXPFGCDN_EL1, Selected Error Pseudo Fault Generation Count Down Register, EL1Register ERXPFGCDN_EL1 accesses the ERR<n>PFGCND register for the error record selected by ERRSELR_EL1.SEL.
ERXPFGCTL_EL1, Selected Error Pseudo Fault Generation Control Register, EL1Register ERXPFGCTL_EL1 accesses the ERR<n>PFGCTL register for the error record selected by ERRSELR_EL1.SEL.
ERXPFGF_EL1, Selected Pseudo Fault Generation Feature Register, EL1Register ERXPFGF_EL1 accesses the ERR<n>PFGF register for the error record selected by ERRSELR_EL1.SEL.

p.xref: ACTLR_EL3, Auxiliary Control Register, EL3The ACTLR_EL3 provides IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED configuration and control options for EL3.

AFSR0_EL3, Auxiliary Fault Status Register 0, EL3AFSR0_EL3 provides additional IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED status information for s that are taken to EL3. In the Cortexâ€‘A76 , no additional information is provided for these s. Therefore this register is not used.
AFSR1_EL3, Auxiliary Fault Status Register 1, EL3AFSR1_EL3 provides additional IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED status information for s that are taken to EL3. This register is not used in the Cortexâ€‘A76 .

AMAIR_EL3, Auxiliary Memory Attribute Indirection Register, EL3AMAIR_EL3 provides IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED memory attributes for the memory s specified by MAIR_EL3. This register is not used in the Cortexâ€‘A76 .
CPTR_EL3, Architectural Feature Trap Register, EL3The CPTR_EL3 controls trapping to EL3 of access to CCR_EL1, CPTR_EL2, trace functionality and registers associated with and execution.
MDCR_EL3, Monitor Debug Configuration Register, EL3The MDCR_EL3 provides configuration options for Security to self-hosted debug.
R_EL3, Reset Management RegisterThe R_EL3 controls the execution state that the boots into and allows request of a Warm reset.
RVBAR_EL3, Reset Vector Base Address Register, EL3RVBAR_EL3 contains the IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED address that execution starts from after reset.

R_EL1, Physical Address Register, EL1The R_EL1 returns the output address from an address translation instruction that executed successfully, or information if the instruction did not execute successfully.
